# Visualize doublets from Scrublet
# Doublet analysis did not reveal a bimodal curve. Therefore, I downloaded file with no threshold, just to visualize the doublet score. We expect 419 doublets to be there
dwhite_10=read.csv(file = "/home/rstudio/time-series/scrublet/white_10.csv")
swhite_10@meta.data$doublet_score=dwhite_10$doublet_score
FeaturePlot(swhite_10,"doublet_score")


# From looking at doublet score, no real distint cluster looks like a doublet. I am going to cluster cells now and see if the number of cells and umi detected in any cluster may correspond to doublet. 
# Ans: Identified cluster 2 at res 0.5 with ~1.5-2X UMI count. The cluster has ~ 584 cells, which is comparable to expected 419 cells. However, doublets score was comparable to cluster 0 and 1 at res 0.5. I will be filtering this cluster anyway for high mt content. 
# Ans: These cluster 2 cells were identified as doublets between cluster 0 and 5, and were also picked to be doublets by doublet detection tool.

# Visualize doublets from doublet detection
# We expect 419 doublets to be there. Detected 440
dwhite_10 <- read.table("/home/rstudio/time-series/doublet_detection/white_10.txt", quote="\"", comment.char="")
swhite_10@meta.data$doublet=dwhite_10$V1  
FeaturePlot(swhite_10,"doublet")

# Visualize cells clustered at different resolutions
library(ggplot2)
p=list(length(seq(0.1, .6, by = .05)))
x=1
for (i in seq(0.1, .6, by = .05)) {
  col.name=colnames(swhite_10@meta.data)[match(paste("RNA_snn_scVI_res",i,sep = "."),colnames(swhite_10@meta.data))]
  p[[x]]=UMAPPlot(swhite_10,group.by=col.name,label=TRUE)+ggtitle(col.name)
  x=x+1
}
